HEADWORD: Retund
<hw>Re*tund"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>retundere</ets>, <ets>retusum</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- +
<ets>tundere</ets> to beat.]</ety> <def>To blunt; to turn, as an edge;
figuratively, to cause to be obtuse or dull; <as>as, to <ex>retund</ex>
confidence</as>.</def> <rj><au>Ray. Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

